args:
Pleased to make your acquaintance,
you two. And you must be Tf-997, the
rubbish from the Synthetic Shapeshifting
Project.
I am Bauer. I believe our meeting will\nbe short-lived, but I am delighted to\nmeet you.
Heh heh... You'll find I'm not quite as soft\nas the Doctor.
You could number a thousand and still be\nno match for me.
Oh, I know that quite well.
We will now commence field testing of the\nsubject. Men, take your positions!
We're surrounded! Wh-what should we do,\nAldred?
Just stay close. This is nothing.
You think circling up is all it'll take to\nbeat me? You underestimate my power.
And you underestimate ours. These are\nmerely the walls of the arena, my mangled\nfriend.
Ij-458. A modified fiend, made using the\nsame concepts seen in Ij-9.
Humanoids like Ij-9 have certain limits\nto their strength, but fiends are more\nflexible.

Case in point, Ij-9 was only able to accept
the dragon mana transfusion in her right
armâ€”but Ij-458 has done so in 14
different areas.
As such, we expect Ij-458's abilities to\nfar surpass Ij-9's.
Of course, it can still be a bit...unruly.\nBut the data we collect from this trial\nshould help us remedy that.
So you plan to feed me to it, like a mouse\nto a snake.
You should be honored to die for the\ncause of the Syndicate!

So that's Bauer's new toy, huh?
I don't care what its stats are on paper.
Strength ain't something you can measure
with numbers alone.
What is he DOING?!\nI know he's stronger than that!
Ngh... Dammit...\nGuess I have to use wyâ€”aaaaaagh!
Aldred! He's used too much of his power...\nHis body can't take it!
Ugh, what's going on?!\nCan he not use his power?
If he gets wasted this easily, imagine how\nthat'll make ME look...
Heh heh. I believe that's the match.
What is the meaning of this, Ij-9?\nThis is hardly something I can overlook.
I know, I... I guess my body just moved\non its own.
I see. So it was just an accident, then?
Yeah. My right arm, it just... I don't know.\nI lost control of it for a second.
I see. Well, no harm done.
...Is what you would no doubt like to hear!
I have no tolerance for those who would\nobstruct the work of the Syndicate.
Hey, come on, I just scratched up your\ntoy a bit! It ain't that big a deal, right?
The Syndicate does not forgive treachery,\nIj-9. Your freedom ends here.
Bellina. Let me ask you something.
Make it quick, Aldred.\nI don't have time for failures.
Look, I wasn't TRYING to save you, okay?\nI just didn't wanna watch you get beat\naround anymore.

Maybe it's because you weren't fit to fight.
Maybe it's that army that had you
surrounded while you got pummeled.
Something just didn't sit right.
...Do you think we can cut our way out?
Hah. Weren't you just yelling about how\na thousand men couldn't take you down?
Oh yeah? 'Cause I could take down a\nthousand guys no problem!
If I wasn't injured, I could take out\nTEN thousandâ€”in only ten blows!
Excuse me, but I don't think now is the\ntime for a battle of boasts!
You have a plan, I take it?
You'll owe me for this. Once we make it\nout of here and I take care of a few things,\nI'll turn my sights on you.
I'll defeat you and prove that I'm number\noneâ€”the freest of all.\nYou won't know what hit you!
A dust cloud?! *cough* *cough* I can't\nsee anything!
What theâ€”who pushed me?!\nStay in formation!
They won't have gotten far.\nSplit up and find them!
Cling to your freedom all you like, Ij-9.\nIn the end, I hold it in the palm of\nmy hand...
